The paper discusses the use of Entity Linking (EL) to improve the retrieval effectiveness in microblogging, which is a subfield of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques such as Named Entity Recognition (NER) and Part-of-Speech (POS) tagging, which are commonly used in Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of knowledge bases such as Wikipedia, which is a topic in Semantic Web (cs.SI) and Database (cs.DB) subfields. Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of real-time filtering, which can be relevant to Cybersecurity (cs.CY) subfield.
